HEADWORD: oeil-de-boeuf
<hw>oeil`-de-boeuf"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>oeils-de-boeuf</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[F., lit., eye of an
ox.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A circular or oval window; --
generally used of architecture of the 17th and 18th centuries. A famous
room in the palace of Versailles bears this name, from the oval window
opening into it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

